 There are some who did not pass and might have to repeat grade 12. It is not easy to dealing with not passing. Lowvelder has put together tips on how to cope with failing:
Learn from your failure
– Judging yourself will not help you.
Stay ambitious
– Do not give up your hopes and dreams, over time your failure will become a distant memory. Share your journey with others
– This will not happen right away with time try sharing your story of failure with others.  Bounce back
– Focus on the future and think about ways to get it right the next time.
Talk it out
– Talk it out with your family and friends to cope with failing an exam. Review your study methods
– It may be time to take a serious look at your studying techniques.
Source: www.fabhow.com